By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The national working committee of the Peoples Democratic Party has constituted a 7-man caretaker committee to pilot the affairs of the party in Ebonyi state in line with the provisions of the constitution of the PDP. According to the statement signed by the National Publicity Secretary of the party, Kola Ologbondiyan released via twitter, this followed the dissolution of the Ebonyi State Exco of  our great party. According to the statement, Hon Fred Udeogu is to chair the 7-man committee. See the statement below: